hints_latex:
Remember that the Product Rule states that:

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle
(f(x)\times g(x))'=f'(x)g(x)+f(x)g'(x)
\end{align*}

sols_latex:
Using the Product Rule, we get:

\begin{align*}
f'(x)&=(x\cos{x})'\\
&=(x)'(\cos{x})+x(\cos{x})'\\
&=\cos{x}+x(-\sin{x})\\
&=\cos{x}-x\sin{x}
\end{align*}

